European foulbrood of honey bees, Ecuador
-----------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 19 Jun 2015 from Dr Diego Alfonso Vizcaino Cabezas, [Agricultural Engineer, Minister of Agriculture, Livestock, Aquaculture and Fisheries], Quito, Ecuador

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 22 Apr 2015
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 17 Jun 2015
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: _Melissococcus plutonius_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to whole country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (10): Loja, Amaluza, Espindola, Loja
Date of start of the outbreak: 22 Apr 2015
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: apiary
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Bees (hives) / 19 / 5 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: apiary within the category of medium-sized farms.

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Bees (hives) / 26.32 / 0 / 0 / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comment: The reported outbreak follows findings during active surveillance carried out every year by AGROCALIDAD [Ecuadorian Agency for Agro Quality Assurance] in order to detect the presence and/or absence of bee diseases. The outbreak is being monitored according to the guidelines established in the Procedure Manual for bee diseases of the National Beekeeping Programme. Active surveillance will go on. This finding is located in a province of the country.

Control measures
Measures applied: disinfection/ disinfestation; no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Laboratory of the Directorate for Animal Diagnosis/AGROCALIDAD (national laboratory) / Bees / bacteriological examination / 17 Jun 2015 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

